#
# Per-rig overrides for the slider subprocess.
#
# Sourced from config/sliderconf.tcl at the end of its startup, so the
# slider namespace and its subscriptions to ain/vals and slider/virtual
# are already in place. Use this file to pick which ain channel the
# physical slider is wired to and to set calibration defaults that
# match the pot and workspace on this rig.
#

# --- Input source ------------------------------------------------------
#
# Controls which input path drives slider/position. Prevents the virtual
# slider and real hardware from competing (whichever fires last wins).
#
#   "ain"     - only the ain/vals hardware path publishes (rig default)
#   "virtual" - only the virtual path publishes (dev / simulation)
#   "auto"    - both paths active, last writer wins (default out of box)
#
# On a rig with a wired slider, set to "ain":
# slider::set_source ain
#
# On a dev laptop with no hardware, set to "virtual":
# slider::set_source virtual

# --- Channel mapping ---------------------------------------------------
#
# chan_x = 0 means the slider pot is wired to ain channel 0.
# chan_y = -1 disables the y axis (1D slider setup; the default).
# For a 2D setup (two pots, or a non-centering thumbstick), set chan_y.
#
# slider::set_chan_x 0
# slider::set_chan_y -1

# --- Calibration -------------------------------------------------------
#
# Linear model: out = scale * ((raw - center) minus deadzone), with
# optional invert and symmetric clamp.
#
#   center:    raw ADC value when the slider is at its neutral /
#              experimentally-zero position. For a 12-bit ADC with a
#              symmetric pot wired between 0 and 3.3V, center ~= 2048.
#              Alternatively, park the slider where you want zero and
#              call slider::set_current_as_center.
#
#   scale:     output units per raw ADC count. If your experiment's
#              world uses visual degrees and full pot deflection covers
#              +/- 10 deg of travel, scale = 10.0 / 2048 ~= 0.00488.
#
#   deadzone:  raw ADC counts around center to treat as zero. Useful
#              for cheap pots with noisy rest position.
#
#   invert:    flip the sign of the axis (if the pot is wired such
#              that increasing pot position decreases the output).
#
#   limit:     symmetric clamp on the calibrated output, < 0 to
#              disable. Useful to prevent runaway if the subject
#              deflects to the mechanical stop.
#
# slider::set_center_x   2048.0
# slider::set_scale_x    0.00488
# slider::set_deadzone_x 20.0
# slider::set_invert_x   0
# slider::set_limit_x    10.0

# Print the resulting settings so the log clearly shows the current
# per-rig calibration.
puts "slider (local): [dservGet slider/settings]"
